  "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nAn adversary can easily block bootnodes IPs and our users won't be able to communicate.\r\n\r\nAs a user, I'd like to use Status with custom bootnodes in case Status bootnode IPs are blocked.\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n\r\nProvide a way to distribute new bootnodes to users. Upon scanning a QR code bootnodes should be updated. App restart is OK.\r\n\r\n### Notes\r\n\r\nHardcoded bootnodes: https://github.com/status-im/status-go/blob/develop/geth/params/cluster.go\r\n\r\nCluster config: https://github.com/status-im/status-go/blob/375d5ec8c304e17dedb4358a4222c7742e141c53/geth/params/config.go#L165-L175\r\n\r\nRelated:\r\n- https://github.com/status-im/status-cluster/issues/92\r\n- https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/3994\r\n\r\n<blockquote><img src=\"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/11767950?s=400&v=4\" width=\"48\" align=\"right\"><div><img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/favicon.ico\" height=\"14\"> GitHub</div><div><strong><a href=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-go\">status-im/status-go</a></strong></div><div>status-go - The Status module that consumes go-ethereum</div></blockquote>",
